    pearls: ["ECT is the most effective treatment for severe, treatment-resistant depression with response rates of 50-70% when medications have failed", "Memory loss is the most significant patient concern — anterograde amnesia is usually temporary (weeks), but some retrograde amnesia for events near treatment time may persist", "Right unilateral electrode placement at 6x seizure threshold produces comparable efficacy to bilateral placement with significantly fewer cognitive side effects", "Hold benzodiazepines and anticonvulsants before ECT as they raise seizure threshold and may result in inadequate seizure; caffeine or hyperventilation may be used to lower seizure threshold if needed", "Increased intracranial pressure is the only absolute contraindication for ECT; pheochromocytoma and recent stroke are relative contraindications"],
